pullRequest.body:
New tactic `fun_prop` to prove FUNction PROPerties like continuity, differentiability, ...

---

General tactic for proving function properties(like continuity, differentiability, etc.) which decomposes a function into a composition of many elementary functions which we know the properties of.

Compared to `aesop` is should be significantly faster and hopefully also works in more cases.

Special attention has been taken such that it works with bundled morphisms and that it can infer for example continuity from differentiability while still maintaining performance.

An example file how to set up `fun_prop` to prove `Measurable f` can be found [here](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/lecopivo/fprop/test/fun_prop.lean). More comprehensive test file is [here](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/lecopivo/fprop/test/fun_prop_dev.lean).
